Today we learned about cybersecurity. 
What is cybersecurity-is the practice of protecting systems, networks, and programs from digital attacks. 
Why is cybersecurity important? 
Cyberattacks can access, change, or destroy sensitive information
Cyberattacks can disrupt business processes
Cyberattacks can extort money from users via ransomware
How do we protect against cyberattacks? 
Use firewalls
Use anti-virus and anti-malware programs
Use data loss prevention (DLP)s
Use other multi-layered threat prevention technologies
Configure security settings within individual apps
Resolve bugs in code
